ient.render`) to align tests with the same serialised bytes consumers see; `inProcessTransport({...})` auto-defaults `fileSystem` to `fromMemoryFs()` when none is supplied so headless/test consumers (`createNodeClient` + `replicad()` + `esbuild()`) keep working zero-config without wiring a transport+filesystem pair — without this default tests fail with `filesystem not available - initialize must complete first with fileSystemPort`; the descriptor records whether the FS is auto-defaulted vs user-supplied so explicit `fromNodeFs()` / `fromMemoryFs()` overrides still win

